snippet.textDisplay:
Cool... but Muslim, White and Mexican aren’t ethnicities. One’s a religion, the other a race and the last one a nationality.

Any ethnicity can be Muslim, though it’s usually Arabs, Berbers, Moors, Persians, etc.

White can include Mediterranean (in which I’m including Italy, Greece, Spain, and maybe France, Celtic, Germanic (which includes Anglo-Saxons and possibly France as well), Scandinavian and Slavic (i.e., most of Eastern Europe)

And Mexican can include any race, ethnicity or religion. Though most Mexicans, myself included, are mestizos, which means we’re a mixture of European and Native American. I, personally, am likely to have a bit of Otomi or Pame ancestry, as well as Spanish and maybe even Lebanese
